channel.title: Compiler.bat problem
channel.description:
Hi guys, I'm kinda, or well, really new here, and I don't have any Java knowledge, unfortunately. I am trying to make a private server, obviously. I have tried compiling several servers but with every server I get this:
Note: Some input files are unchecked or unsafe operations. Note: Recompile with -Xlint:unchecked for details.
I have the path to my JDK right (at least, I hope so): C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.7.0\bin\javac.exe
Here is what I see when I open the compiler with notepad:
[code]@echo off "C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.7.0\bin\javac.exe" -classpath deps/log4j-
1.2.15.jar;deps/jython.jar;deps/xstream.jar;deps/mina.jar;deps/mysql.jar;deps/poi.
jar;deps/slf4j.jar;deps/slf4j-nop.jar -d bin src\server\event\*.java
src\server\model\items\*.java src\server\model\minigames\*.java
src\server\model\npcs\*.java src\server\model\objects\*.java
src\server\model\players\*.java src\server\model\players\skills\*.java
src\server\model\players\packets\*.java src\server\model\shops\*.java
src\server\net\*.java src\server\task\*.java src\server\util\*.java
src\server\world\*.java src\server\util\log\*.java src\server\*.java
src\server\world\map\*.java pause[/code]
(I am using the Insidia source, latest version).
Any solutions? Suggestions are highly appreciated too.
- Bitterlemon
EDIT - I have seen something similar in the common compiler errors post, but it's not exactly the same. Is this actually an error or just a warning?

item.title: Compiler.bat problem
item.dc:creator: @demps2k9 demps2k9
item.description:
@demps2k9 wrote:

[quote=“Bitterlemon, post:6, topic:412769”]Still the same.
When I run the Insidia server and my MoparScape client, I can’t actually get in, so I thought it had something to do with this. Apparently not
But do you guys have any solutions on that? Isn’t my server connected to my client or something?
Yeah, you can :fp:, but I don’t know anything about this, and that is actually the reason I’m making a private, I just wanna learn more about this.

I’m getting the error “No response from loginserver Please wait 1 minute and try again”.
Waiting does obviously not help.[/quote]

That is because the server doesn’t support the clients packets.
